org.apache.beam.sdk.util

Class AppliedCombineFn<K,InputT,AccumT,OutputT>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.beam.sdk.util.AppliedCombineFn<K,InputT,AccumT,OutputT>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - type of keys
    InputT - type of input values
    AccumT - type of mutable accumulator values
    OutputT - type of output values
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class AppliedCombineFn<K,InputT,AccumT,OutputT>
extends Object
implements Serializable
    A CombineWithContext.KeyedCombineFnWithContext with a fixed accumulator coder. This is created from a specific application of the CombineWithContext.KeyedCombineFnWithContext.

    Because the AccumT may reference InputT, the specific Coder<AccumT> may depend on the Coder<InputT>.
